  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TRM Concept, Objectives, and Initial Planning Workshop. Mitigation &amp; AAR Workshop. TRM Planning Coordination Workshop. TRM TTX and Planning Workshop for Doctrine Review. International Joint Bioterrorism Response. TRM Final Planning Workshop</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthen the global community&apos;s ability to safely destroy, store, apply safeguards to, and transport weapons of mass destruction (WMD) and secure related facilities and materials; control borders and territory to prevent illicit movement of WMD and related materials and technology and to prosecute and punish violators; prevent the proliferation of WMD and related materials, technology, and expertise to states or non-state actors of concern or to potential terrorists; comply fully with international obligations concerning arms control, nonproliferation, and WMD terrorism; deter and prevent WMD terrorism; and respond to a WMD terrorism event.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This award strives to strengthen the global community&apos;s ability to safely destroy, store, apply safeguards to, and transport weapons of mass destruction (WMD) and secure related facilities and materials. More specifically, this includes DTRA ICP conducted an initial planning workshop with Filipino government representatives to assess capability gaps in countering WMD proliferation in the maritime domain.. DTRA ICP conducted a mitigation and after-action review workshop with Filipino government representatives to assess capability gaps in countering WMD proliferation in the maritime domain.. DTRA ICP conducted a planning coordination workshop with Filipino government representatives to assess capability gaps in countering WMD proliferation in the maritime domain.. DTRA ICP conducted a tabletop exercise and planning workshop with Filipino government representatives to assess capability gaps in countering WMD proliferation in the maritime domain.. DTRA ICP delivered joint training to 36 mid-level Filipino public health and law enforcement authorities responsible for deterring, detecting, identifying, and responding to a bioterrorism incident with a broad overview of bioterrorism and its relationship to WMD proliferation.. DTRA ICP conducted a final planning workshop with Filipino government representatives to assess capability gaps in countering WMD proliferation in the maritime domain..</narrative>
  </description>
